ht to the central regions of the ULX. The pattern of\nspectral variability with luminosity in two ULXs that straddle the hard/soft\nultraluminous regime boundary is consistent with the wind increasing at higher\naccretion rates, and thus narrowing the opening angle of the funnel. Hence,\nthis work suggests that most ULXs can be explained as stellar-mass black holes\naccreting at and above the Eddington limit, with their observed characteristics\ndominated by two variables: accretion rate and inclination. (abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Jul 2013 16:57:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
